description: 'Murder, Forsooth' is the way Shakespeare might have put it when Honey goes undercover at a Medieval Faire (dressed in a corset and push-up bra!), to find out who's threatening to kill the May Queen. And when those beauty queens go at it tooth and nail - battling for a prize that could lead to stardom, in a contest that might very well be fixed - woe betide the girl who wins, because her jealous rivals might make sure that it's adios, hasta la vista, so long - at the Faire!
name: Murder, Forsooth!, Part One, Chapter 1: So Long at the Faire

description:
Angels...gods...demons. Earth's past is filled with tales of immortals who ruled over common men. For centuries man has lived under the impression that these stories were all fantasies and fairy tales. But the time has come when they will be proven true and powerful immortals will walk among normal men again... and look to take their rightful place as rulers. A new chapter in the Grimm Universe begins here.

Note: The Goblin Queen only appears on an alternate cover.
name: 2012 Annual

description: THE COUNTDOWN TO GRIMM FAIRY TALES #75 CONTINUES Sela's struggle to find the last remaining portal in the realm of Myst has finally led her to the Tomb of Death. Now all that stands between her and the portal is the evil entity behind the corruption of the land: The Winter Witch. This issue leads up to the epic Grimm Fairy Tales #75 anniversery issue. Don't miss out!
name: Winter's End
